# Swipe File

A library of **analogous copy from other businesses** that lands well on similar buyers. Reference material for when you're drafting your own copy and want to pattern-match what works.

> Copy to `swipe-file.md` (drop the `.template` suffix). Add an entry whenever you encounter copy in the wild that genuinely lands on someone like your buyer.

---

## Why this exists

You write better copy when you can pattern-match against examples that resonate, vs. trying to invent voice from scratch every time. The swipe file is a curated set of "this is the right shape for my audience."

Don't include things that are merely *good* — only things that hit your specific buyer's nervous system. Quality bar: would *your* buyer read this and lean in?

---

## Entry template

```
## Entry N: <short name>

**Source:** <URL or reference>
**Captured:** YYYY-MM-DD
**What it sells:** <short description of the actual offering>
**Audience overlap with mine:** <high / medium / low — and why>

### What's working

- <pattern 1 — e.g. "leads with the problem in the buyer's exact language">
- <pattern 2 — e.g. "names what it isn't, not just what it is">
- <pattern 3 — e.g. "concrete result with a number, not a vague benefit">

### Pull-quotes worth borrowing

> "<exact quote 1>"
> "<exact quote 2>"

### How I'd adapt for my work

<1–3 sentences naming the structural move you'd take and how it'd land for your audience>
```

