## Entry 1: <<EDIT: first example>>

<<EDIT — example structure:

**Source:** https://example.com/landing
**Captured:** YYYY-MM-DD
**What it sells:** <product>
**Audience overlap with mine:** medium — same nervous-system signals (overwhelm + bottleneck), different surface (eCommerce vs. services)

### What's working

- Headline names the problem in the buyer's exact phrasing ("you can't take a real day off")
- The "for / not for" section is unusually direct — turns away the wrong fit explicitly
- Pricing page leads with what it includes BEFORE the number

### Pull-quotes worth borrowing

> "If you've ever opened your laptop on vacation, this is for you."
> "We don't sell software. We sell the relief of not being on call."

### How I'd adapt for my work

The "for / not for" section is the highest-leverage move for me — my audience self-qualifies harder than they buy.
>>

